sketch.util

Class DLListElement

  • java.lang.Object
    • sketch.util.AssertedClass
      • sketch.util.DLListElement

  • public class DLListElement
extends AssertedClass
    ListElement is used to keep track of elements of a List. Every list has a single element, which is the root of the list. Root's nextElem points to the first element in the list, and prevElem points to the last element in the list. It can be easily distinguished from all other elements because its data member points to itself.

      • next

        public DLListElement next()
        Return the next element in the list. Checks that the current element is not the root of the list (the root does not have a next element!)

      • prev

        public DLListElement prev()
        Return the prev element in the list. Checks that the prev element is not the root of the list (root element is not a prev element for any element)

      • get

        public java.lang.Object get()
